class_notes: This course is intended for non-science majors and will cover the principles of genetics, physiology, ecology, taxonomy, and evolution with special reference to contemporary life situations. Students under the old GERs must also register for a laboratory section.  Students under the new GERs may take the optional laboratory, if desired.  This course DOES NOT FULFILL requirements for medical and dental schools or for a biology major. No prerequisites.
